725292f-a.text:
Thirty-ninth Avenue, a south side, east from No. 39 opposite Prince Street, showing a gray house in the foreground which was the Rectory of the St. George Episcopal Church. It was erected in 1879. Rev. H.D. Waller was a one time resident in this house.
1922
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection
